snippet.title: Intro to vectors & scalars | One-dimensional motion | Physics | Khan Academy
snippet.description:
Distance, displacement, speed and velocity. Difference between vectors and scalars. Created by Sal Khan.

Watch the next lesson: https://www.khanacademy.org/science/physics/one-dimensional-motion/displacement-velocity-time/v/calculating-average-velocity-or-speed?utm_source=YT&utm_medium=Desc&utm_campaign=physics

Missed the previous lesson? https://www.khanacademy.o,rg/science/physics/one-dimensional-motion/displacement-velocity-time/v/introduction-to-physics?utm_source=YT&utm_medium=Desc&utm_campaign=physics

Physics on Khan Academy: Physics is the study of the basic principles that govern the physical world around us. We'll start by looking at motion itself. Then, we'll learn about forces, momentum, energy, and other concepts in lots of different physical situations. To get the most out of physics, you'll need a solid understanding of algebra and a basic understanding of trigonometry.

snippet.description:
